  "description": "Advertising consent to display one externally illuminated sign, measuring 6.6m (height) x 5.8m (width) on the southern elevation of 596-598 Kingsland Road, within temporary scaffolding shroud, incorporating a 1:1 facsimile of the building and its architectural features printed on it.&nbsp;",
  "subdivision_of_building": null,
  "actual_completion_date": null,
  "lpa_app_no": "2024/1947",
  "decision": "Approved",
  "application_type_full": "Consent to display an advertisement",
  "last_updated_by": "Portal",
  "appeal_status": null,
  "id": "Hackney-2024_1947",
  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;The development hereby permitted shall only be carried out and completed strictly in accordance with the submitted plans and documents hereby approved and any subsequent approval of details.\r\n&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\r\nREASON: To ensure that the development hereby permitted is carried out in full accordance with the plans hereby approved.\r\n&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;Light from the luminaires shall not exceed 25 EV (lux) when measured at any residential or light sensitive window overlooking the development.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;All luminaries shall be oriented and designed in such a way to minimise light spillage beyond the boundary and prevent glare into the windows of residential or light sensitive properties overlooking the development.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;REASON: To minimise any loss of amenities from potential light pollution.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The existing graffiti located on the southern elevation/flank wall must be removed upon completion of the repair and restoration works.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;REASON: In the interests of visual amenity of the site and the surrounding Dalston Conservation Area and the setting of the listed building at 590-592 Kingsland Road.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The advertisement permitted by this consent is permitted on a temporary basis, for a period of 12 months from the date of this consent, after which date the advert must be removed. If the building works which caused the scaffolding to be required are completed before this date then the advertisement shall be removed from the site on the completion of the works.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;REASON: To enable refurbishment of the building to take place as per the Schedule of Works without resulting in a lasting impact to the conservation area or the setting of the listed buildings.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;1. No advertisement is to be displayed without the permission of the owner of the site or any other person with an interest in the site entitled to grant permission.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;2. No advertisement shall be sited or displayed so as to&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left: 25px;&quot;&gt; (a)endanger persons using any highway, railway, waterway, dock, harbour or aerodrome (civil or military);&lt;br&gt;(b)obscure, or hinder the ready interpretation of, any traffic sign, railway signal or aid to navigation by water or air; or&lt;br&gt;(c)hinder the operation of any device used for the purpose of security or surveillance or for measuring the speed of any vehicle.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;3. Any advertisement displayed, and any site used for the display of advertisements, shall be maintained in a condition that does not impair the visual amenity of the site.\r\n&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\r\n4. Any structure or hoarding erected or used principally for the purpose of displaying advertisements shall be maintained in a condition that does not endanger the public.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\r\n\r\n5. Where an advertisement is required under these Regulations to be removed, the site shall be left in a condition that does not endanger the public or impair visual amenity.&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
